title: SCI-FI - A Century of Science Fiction - Star Wars vs Star Trel
description:
ReQuest - Audiobooks - Docubook

A CENTURY OF SCIENCE FICTION FEATURING STAR WARS VS STAR TREK

It is a fierce and embroiled battle between Star Wars and Star Trek - fans choosing sides while box office receipts and merchandise sales soar sky high. A Century of Science Fiction compares the space opera worlds of George Lucas and Gene Roddenberry for a one-of-a-kind intergalactic documentary. Interviews with such stars as William Shatner, George Lucas, Leonard Nimoy, Anthony Daniels, Billy Dee Williams, Carrie Fisher, James Doohan and many more help to explain the amazing phenomenon, Whether you\&#039;re a Trekkie or a Jedi Knight, this is one Docubook you won\&#039;t want to miss!

A Century of Science Fiction also offers a compelling look at Close Encounters and provides the listener with astronishing Proof of Alien Contact. Travel inside AREA 51 with Bob Lazar, a former government scientist, and listen to Former NASA astronaut Gordon Cooper as he breaks his silence and discusses his close encounters with alien craft. The exclusive interviews with Steven Speilberg, Will Smith, Sigourney Weaver, Robert Wise, David Duchovny, and many more will leave you without a doubt to the existence of extraterrestrial life.

3 compact disks/2 hours 25 minutes / ABRIDGED
2006
